title: [IOTDB-5907] Pipe: pipe subtask scheduler
body:
The code is a implementation of a Pipe Subtask Scheduler. 

The purpose of this code is to schedule subtasks to be executed based on certain criteria. The scheduler uses two different checkpoint intervals to decide when to schedule a subtask. The first is based on the number of events consumed by the subtask, and the second is based on the time duration since the last checkpoint. The code adjusts these checkpoint intervals based on the current status of the executor, such as the number of running subtasks and the core pool size. 

The scheduler also has a reset function to schedule the subtasks from scratch.

body:
Function description:
Add configuration item (backupNodeurlsbackupUsernamebackupPassword) to configure the main cluster IP and backup cluster IP, where the main cluster IP is required (can have more than one IP, required) and the backup cluster IP is optional (can have more than one IP, optional)

Function definition:

When the primary cluster is normally connected, the client connects to the primary cluster
When the primary cluster is disconnected, it switches to the backup cluster
When the primary cluster is reconnected, it switches to the primary cluster again

Create a new HASessionPool, use the same as SessionPool,
Example
List<String> nodeUrls = new ArrayList<>(); nodeUrls.add("127.0.0.1:6667"); nodeUrls.add("127.0.0.1:6668"); List<String> backupNodeUrls = new ArrayList<>(); backupNodeUrls.add("172.20.31.10:6667"); backupNodeUrls.add("172.20.31.10:6668"); HASessionPool pool = new HASessionPool.Builder() .nodeUrls(nodeUrls) .user("root") .password("root") .backupNodeUrls(nodeUrls) .backupUser("root") .backupPassword("root") .maxSize(3) .build();

title: [IOTDB-5796][IOTDB-5701] Remove recorder and optimize the usage of metrics
body:
This PR is mainly focused on the metric module and optimizes the implementation of the metric module. The details are as follows.
1. Unify the access of metric service in nodeManager about partition.
2. Optimize the metrics in the IoT Consensus module: optimize access way and related metric sets.
3. Optimize the implementation of the Metric enum, split different metric names into sections, and add a parameter to avoid toString() cost.
4. Optimize the implementation of the Tag, CompactionType, ProcessChunkType, and CheckpointType enum, and add a parameter to avoid toString() cost.
5. Optimize ChunkCacheMetrics and fix class cast.
6. Merge CacheMetrics and CacheMetricsRecorder to manage partition cache-related metrics.
7. Merge CompactionMetrics and CompactionManage to manage compaction-related metrics. At the same time, fix 2 problems that are forgetting to divide 1024 in the read scenario and forgetting to update the summary before updation.
8. Merge Writing Metrics and WritingMetircsManager to manage writing-related metrics.
9. Merge query-related metrics with QueryMetricManager to reduce cost.

title: [IOTDB-5889] Fix not releasing readlock of TsFile when fail to allocate memory for compaction
body:
See [IOTDB-5889](https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/IOTDB-5889).

The reason for this bug is that when the compaction task failed to allocate enough memory to starts, the system will throw an exception and just abort the task. But when the task is aborted, the status of tsfile resource doesn't change from COMPACTING to NROMAL, and the read lock doesn't get released. As a result of that, TTL thread failed to get the write lock of the tsfile and fail to delete the file.

This PR fix the bug by changing the order of compaction task starting process from 
```Getting Readlock -> Changing file status -> Allocating memory```
to
```Allocating memory -> Getting readlock -> Changing file status```

title: [IOTDB-5884] Throw Exception when alter template with duplicate measurement
body:
## Description


### Problem

When there's duplicate measurement in one template extension request, there's no exception returned but the request is executed successfully and the registered measurement is the first one.

### Cause

When extending schema template on configNode, the measurement duplication will be ignored and the first one takes effect.

### Solution

Add duplication check on dataNode before sending RPC request to configNode.
Add deduplication in template auto extension during data insertion with insert records or tablets or TsFile load.

title: [IOTDB-5877] Fix StringIndexOutOfBoundsException when invoking Session.createTimeseriesUsingSchemaTemplate with list contains null
body:
## Description


### Cause
The null in RPC request cannot be recognized by Thrift, thus resulting in StringIndexOutOfBoundsException.


### Solution
Add null check in session and return more readable msg.

title: [IOTDB-5872] Reduce some IoTConsensus index logs
body:
## Description

#### In a long-running cluster, most of the logs are related to the index, reducing the number of index logs can help reduce the number of logs.
- Change the print length of the index log segment from 1000 to 10000.
- Deleted index persistence when synchronization was completed.

title: [To rel/1.1][IOTDB-5871]Prevent large seq files from participating cross space compaction
body:
- Add UT to ensure that when the sequence file list is empty, the compaction will not report an error.

- To avoid serious write amplification caused by cross space compaction, we limit that seq files are no longer be compacted when the size reaches the threshold.

title: [To master][IOTDB-5868]Automatically synchronize all node urls in the cluster
body:
When enableRedirection=true, a thread will be started to scan for node additions and deletions once a day by default, automatically completing all nodeurl within the node.

Design documentation: https://timechor.feishu.cn/docx/HUaNdU83YofVQBxyvVocIlk1n1c

New MethodSession/SessionPool.setCheckNodeUrlTimeMs(1000),represents the nodeurl of the nodes in the cluster synchronized every 1000 milliseconds, default is 1 day

title: Add metrics for thread cpu consumption
body: # Dashboard The dashboard contains serveral panel, including thread pool cpu usage percentage, module cpu usage percentage, thread pool user mode(vs kernel mode) percentage, module user mode percentage, thread pool core size, thread pool active thread count, thread pool done task count, thread pool waiting task count. ![image](https://github.com/apache/iotdb/assets/37140360/53f9b533-a2b5-4384-b031-322450b4a697) ![image](https://github.com/apache/iotdb/assets/37140360/86af4008-b16d-4c81-be5c-0a10d02de527) ![image](https://github.com/apache/iotdb/assets/37140360/0e16cc98-8580-47da-bd4b-c7bea3f14646) ![image](https://github.com/apache/iotdb/assets/37140360/d3aeae49-9ce4-4b13-89a6-afc7fe51d677) # Performance issue I have done performance comparsion between this branch and master branch(commit: 1392e03b21ff6c1a792ccef9886a45325ea12a75) using IoT Benchmark in the same environment(8C 32G 5TB HDD) in **standalone mode**. I changed the default pull period for Prometheus from 15 seconds to 10 seconds in order to make the performance issues as obvious as possible. The result is shown as follow: ## master branch ## cpu-metrics ## Conclusion There is nearly no effect on write throughput and query ops of the system.

title: [To rel/1.1][IOTDB-5867]Build device time index when validating tsfiles after compaction
body: In order to strengthen the accuracy of compaction, all tsfiles will be checked for time range of devices to determine whether there is overlap. If it is fileTimeIndex, it needs to be upgraded to deviceTimeIndex.

title: [IOTDB-5867]Build device time index when validating tsfiles after compaction

title: Optimize measurementId serialization in WAL
body: ## Description The String of measurementId comes from Thrift and it should always be UTF-8 encoding. Change the method of String.getBytes can skip the redundant UTF-8 encoding in WAL serialization. Before: After: TSBS write test result: Before: 2024417.61 metrics/sec After: 2182944.86 metrics/sec

This PR contains:
- Default connector of Pipe system
  this connector supports: 1. handshake, 2. transfer insertnode, 3. transfer tsfile with function of resume from break point
- PipeReceiveAgent to accept thrift request from connector
- A simple implement of a handler which can handle thrift request from connector

This PR is for fixing it.
